<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911008-0068</DOCNO><DOCID>911008-0068.</DOCID><HL>   Loral Unit Gets Army Work</HL><DATE>10/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8</SO><CO>   LOR</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><NS>DEFENSE CONTRACTS (DFC)</NS><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>FLORIDA (FL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Loral Corp.'s electro-optical systems unitsaid it was awarded a $35.5 million contract to buildsimulation training equipment for the U.S. Army.   Loral, a New York defense electronics concern, said itexpects the unit to sell $90 million of such simulationtraining equipment by the end of the year.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>